---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="About" description="Learn about the Body Oxygen Level Test (BOLT) and how it can help improve your breathing efficiency">
  <Header slot="header" />
  
  <div class="page-container">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1 class="page-title">About BreatheTrack</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">Understand and improve your breathing efficiency</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="about-content card">
      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>What is the BOLT Score?</h2>
        <p>
          The Body Oxygen Level Test (BOLT) score is a simple self-assessment tool developed by Patrick McKeown, 
          author of "The Oxygen Advantage." It measures your body's tolerance to reduced oxygen and increased carbon dioxide levels, 
          which is indicative of your breathing efficiency.
        </p>
        <p>
          Unlike maximum breath-hold tests, the BOLT test measures the time until your <strong>first</strong> urge to breathe, 
          not how long you can hold your breath in total. This makes it a much safer and more practical tool for regular use.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Why Track Your BOLT Score?</h2>
        <p>Regular monitoring of your BOLT score can help you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Track improvements in breathing patterns</li>
          <li>Gauge the effectiveness of breathing exercises</li>
          <li>Monitor respiratory health</li>
          <li>Understand your body's COâ‚‚ tolerance</li>
          <li>Set goals for breathing improvement</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      
      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Understanding Your Score</h2>
        <div class="score-table">
          <div class="score-row header">
            <div>BOLT Score</div>
            <div>Classification</div>
            <div>Interpretation</div>
          </div>
          <div class="score-row">
            <div><span class="score poor">Below 10</span></div>
            <div>Poor</div>
            <div>May experience frequent breathing difficulties, poor sleep quality, and reduced exercise tolerance</div>
          </div>
          <div class="score-row">
            <div><span class="score fair">10-20</span></div>
            <div>Fair</div>
            <div>Common range for many people; may experience occasional symptoms during exercise or stress</div>
          </div>
          <div class="score-row">
            <div><span class="score good">20-30</span></div>
            <div>Good</div>
            <div>Indicates improved breathing patterns; fewer breathing-related symptoms</div>
          </div>
          <div class="score-row">
            <div><span class="score very-good">30-40</span></div>
            <div>Very Good</div>
            <div>Excellent breathing efficiency; good exercise tolerance</div>
          </div>
          <div class="score-row">
            <div><span class="score excellent">40+</span></div>
            <div>Excellent</div>
            <div>Optimal breathing efficiency; typically seen in well-trained athletes</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      
      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Improving Your BOLT Score</h2>
        <p>
          With consistent practice of proper breathing techniques, most people can improve their BOLT score over time. 
          Some effective methods include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Nasal breathing:</strong> Practice breathing through your nose both day and night</li>
          <li><strong>Reduced breathing:</strong> Practice gentle breath reduction exercises</li>
          <li><strong>Breath holds:</strong> Incorporate gentle breath holds into daily activities</li>
          <li><strong>Physical exercise:</strong> Regular exercise with proper breathing technique</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="disclaimer">
          <strong>Note:</strong> Always consult with a healthcare provider before starting any new breathing practice, 
          especially if you have underlying health conditions.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section class="about-section">
        <h2>About BreatheTrack</h2>
        <p>
          BreatheTrack was developed to help individuals track their breathing efficiency using the BOLT method. 
          This application allows you to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Take the BOLT test with a precisely timed interface</li>
          <li>Record and save your results</li>
          <li>Track your progress over time</li>
          <li>Understand your breathing patterns</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          All your data is stored locally on your device. We believe in privacy-first design and do not collect 
          or transmit any personal information.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <Footer slot="footer" />
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .about-content {
    max-width: 800px;
  }
  
  .about-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  
  .about-section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  
  .about-section h2 {
    color: #1f2937;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
  
  .about-section p {
    color: #4b5563;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  
  .about-section ul {
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  
  .about-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  
  .score-table {
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  
  .score-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 2fr;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
  }
  
  .score-row.header {
    background-color: #f9fafb;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #374151;
  }
  
  .score-row:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  
  .score-row > div {
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }
  
  .score-row > div:not(:last-child) {
    border-right: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
  }
  
  .score {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: white;
  }
  
  .score.poor {
    background-color: #ef4444;
  }
  
  .score.fair {
    background-color: #f59e0b;
  }
  
  .score.good {
    background-color: #10b981;
  }
  
  .score.very-good {
    background-color: #3b82f6;
  }
  
  .score.excellent {
    background-color: #6366f1;
  }
  
  .disclaimer {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background-color: #fff7ed;
    border-left: 4px solid #f97316;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .score-table {
      font-size: 0.875rem;
    }
    
    .score-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
    
    .score-row > div:nth-child(3) {
      grid-column: 1 / 3;
      border-right: none;
      border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    }
    
    .score-row.header > div:nth-child(3) {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>
